Plans are in the works for providing educational materials and meals to our students at home! We will be communicating these plans to everyone in the next day or so as the details are worked out. These plans will include distributing materials, supplies and technology to our students at the elementary.

If your student has personal items in their cubbies (gym shoes, coats, rest towels, etc.) that you want to pick up today, the elementary building will be open until 7 PM. If there is a personal item you believe is in their classroom, please make arrangements with the office to pick up those items. Otherwise, all other general school supplies will be distributed at a later time.

Thanks,
Mrs. Lambert

post_text:
Dear AMS Parents,

As you know, as of 11:59 PM this evening, residents of The State of Ohio are subject to stay at home orders issued by Governor Dewine to prevent the spread of COVID-19.

In the near future, Archbold Schools will be announcing specific plans for providing at home education during this difficult time. This will include plans distributing technology to families to be used at home.

In the meantime, many students left school supplies in their lockers, such as workbooks, notebooks, that will be needed during at home instruction.

Prior to the Governor’s orders going into effect, Archbold Middle School will be open from noon to 9 PM today. Families are encouraged to take all supplies and belongings from their student's locker home today. 7th and 8th grade Science classrooms will also be open. Students are encouraged to take their workbooks directly from these rooms

After today, access to the building will be restricted indefinitely.
text:

As you know, as of 11:59 PM this evening, residents of The State of Ohio are subject to stay at home orders issued by Governor Dewine to prevent the spread of COVID-19.

In the near future, Archbold Schools will be announcing specific plans for providing at home education during this difficult time. This will include plans distributing technology to families to be used at home.

In the meantime, many students left school supplies in their lockers, such as workbooks, notebooks, that will be needed during at home instruction.

Prior to the Governor’s orders going into effect, Archbold Middle School will be open from noon to 9 PM today. Families are encouraged to take all supplies and belongings from their student's locker home today. 7th and 8th grade Science classrooms will also be open. Students are encouraged to take their workbooks directly from these rooms

After today, access to the building will be restricted indefinitely.

Your help is needed!

Archbold Community officials have started the process to update the Archbold community’s comprehensive plan. The purpose of the comprehensive plan is to create a shared vision for the community to preserve and build on its heritage while giving direction for desirable growth and development.

You can start doing your part to plan Archbold by taking a community survey that can be found by clicking here: https://s.zoomerang.com/r/ArchboldCommunitySurvey

Make plans to also attend the Community Forum coming up March 30, 6:30 pm, in the Archbold High School cafeteria.
